ai_summary.summary: Participants expressed mixed experiences with the online grocery platform prototype, mainly focusing on the voucher application system. Many encountered initial confusion regarding the application process due to unclear UI distinctions between 'Claim' and 'Use Now' options. Despite initial challenges, participants showcased positive sentiment towards design versions that prioritize ease of use, visibility of voucher options, and a more intuitive interface. The preference for simplified, direct-access voucher management and automatic application features was a recurring theme across feedback, emphasizing the need for a user-friendly approach to enhance overall customer experience.

section.text: There were multiple suggestions for implementing an auto-apply feature for vouchers to reduce steps and enhance user experience.
I love that you're trying to improve the page.

After you have tried the 2 designs, which one do you think is better? Please give your feedback on the design difference:

Version A: Using 2 tabs to separate 2 types of vouchers on the same page

Version B: Using 2 pages for "claim vouchers" and "Your vouchers"

Please speak out loud to tell us why you think A or B is better.

*Click "Your vouchers" and "Claim vouchers" to toggle between the 2 voucher pages

*Switch via the bottom buttons to toggle between different designs.

tasks.description: Would you think it's helpful to have the "use now" button on the front page? It will show you a list of eligible items without seeing the voucher details. Remember to speak out loud to let us know why.

settings.intro_text:
Welcome! We're excited to have you join our test. Please read the instructions carefully before beginning each task.


We'll show you a prototype of the FairPrice app to test the voucher experience. During the study, give your feedback by speaking out loud all your thoughts and suggestions as you follow the instructions to perform each task.


*Only test-related links are clickable in the prototype
settings.complete_text: Thank you for participating in our user study, your feedback has been received. Your participation will help improve this product!
